# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Qinawy — Production environment
# Copy to `.env.production` when building, then `npm run build`.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# API base path (leave as-is if backend is on same domain under /api)
VITE_API_URL=/api

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google AdSense (optional — leave blank to disable ads entirely)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Apply at https://adsense.google.com (site must be live and have content).
# 2. Wait for approval (can take 1-4 weeks).
# 3. Paste your publisher ID below (format: ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX).
# 4. Create 3 ad units in AdSense: "Display/Inline", "In-feed", "Sidebar".
#    Copy each slot ID into the 3 vars below.
# 5. In AdSense → Brand safety → Content → ENABLE restricted categories:
#    Sexually suggestive, Gambling, Alcohol, Tobacco, Weapons.
# 6. Rebuild and redeploy: `npm run build` (in frontend/).
# If these are empty, the <AdSlot /> renders NOTHING — zero impact on UX.

VITE_ADSENSE_CLIENT=
VITE_ADSENSE_SLOT_INLINE=
VITE_ADSENSE_SLOT_INFEED=
VITE_ADSENSE_SLOT_SIDEBAR=

# Future: Other ad networks can be wired the same way
# (e.g. Propeller Ads, Ezoic, Media.net) by extending AdSlot.jsx.
